cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL. 

The paper deals with data-driven models for text summarization and title generation tasks, which are primarily related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes data efficiency metrics, which are relevant to optimization and performance evaluation of ML models, indicating a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Transformer, a popular deep learning architecture, suggests a possible association with cs.DL (Deep Learning) as well. Finally, the paper involves processing and releasing a large dataset of scientific articles, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
